# WPHubPro Bridge — PHP (`includes/`)

## Autoloader (do not bypass)

- Registration lives in `src/Autoloader.php`: prefix `WPHubPro\`, base path `includes/`.
- **PSR-4 mapping**: `WPHubPro\{SubNamespace}\{Class}` → `includes/{SubNamespace/...}/{Class}.php` (namespace segments = directory segments, one class per file, filename = class name + `.php`).
- New classes: add the file under `includes/` matching the namespace; **do not** `require`/`require_once` those classes from other plugin files — rely on `Autoloader::register()` (already bootstrapped from `wphubpro-bridge.php`).
- `Autoloader` itself stays in `src/Autoloader.php` (namespace `WPHubPro`), loaded explicitly before registration.

## PSR-12 and WordPress safety

- Follow [PSR-12](https://www.php-fig.org/psr/psr-12/): `<?php` opening, `declare` if used, `namespace` then `use`, then code; braces and indentation consistent with existing files.
- Keep the standard guard at the top of includable classes:

```php
if ( ! defined( 'ABSPATH' ) ) {
	exit;
}
```

- Prefer `use` imports for class references; match naming and docblock style (`@package WPHubPro`) used in sibling files.

## Current layout (preserve when extending)

Place new code in the same area as related features:

| Area | Path | Namespace examples |
|------|------|-------------------|
| Core / root services | `includes/*.php` | `WPHubPro\` — e.g. `Bridge`, `Config`, `Helper`, `Logger` |
| Admin UI | `includes/Admin/` | `WPHubPro\Admin\` |
| Hub HTTP / REST | `includes/Api/` | `WPHubPro\Api\` |
| Auth / crypto | `includes/Auth/` | `WPHubPro\Auth\` |
| WP-Cron | `includes/Cron/`, `includes/Cron/Job/` | `WPHubPro\Cron\`, `WPHubPro\Cron\Job\` |
| Typed errors | `includes/Error/` | `WPHubPro\Error\` |
| Site health checks | `includes/Health/` | `WPHubPro\Health\` |
| Plugins / updates | `includes/Plugin/` | `WPHubPro\Plugin\` |
| Themes / updates | `includes/Theme/` | `WPHubPro\Theme\` |

- **Subnamespaces** mirror subfolders (e.g. `Cron\Job\Health` → `includes/Cron/Job/Health.php`).
- `includes/**/index.php` files are stubs/security entry points, not autoloaded PSR-4 classes unless they define a real class matching the path (avoid adding class definitions there).

## Debugging

- Use `WPHubPro\Logger` and existing patterns in `includes/Logger.php` / API modules for diagnostics; use structured, grep-friendly messages.
